That's a fair assessment, and again a consequence of quantum algorithms research being driven by computer scientists (which is a good thing).

I would go a bit further and actually say that much of CV quantum computing seems to revolve around mapping DV results to a CV setting. There is, indeed, still a lot of unexplored terrain... Technical Q: what is your take on non-Gaussian gates?

Historically, the computer science community has driven the development of new quantum algorithms, specifically in the qubit gate model. The truth is that CV quantum algorithms are comparatively less explored. Part of my job is to try to change that ;)
I think it's fair to say that @XanaduAI is currently leading the efforts in researching new CV quantum algorithms. You can see some of the latest ideas here https://www. xanadu.ai/research/

Hey Chris! There is no review specifically on CV quantum algorithms that I'm aware of. For references regrading the CV model, see this answer I gave on stackexchange https:// quantumcomputing.stackexchange.com/questions/4166 /what-good-references-would-you-recommend-to-understand-the-continuous-variable/4167#4167 â€¦
